<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-08-25T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-08-25T15:00:00-05:00" n="1351" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1351">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/8–849: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Jones</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">at
                                Nanking</hi><note n="41" xml:id="d1351fn41">Repeated to the Chargé
                                in China as telCan No. 621.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-08-25T16:00:00-04:00">August 25,
                                    1949—4 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1016. Heads mission boards state missionaries in field have full auth
                            make own decisions re evacuation without prior consent hdqrs US. <pb facs="1329" n="1319" xml:id="pg_1319"/> If you have knowledge
                            missionaries desiring leave but awaiting consent hdqrs US which not yet
                            forthcoming pls inform Dept names persons and their mission boards and
                            Dept will bring attn boards concerned. (Embtel 1698, Aug 3<note n="42" xml:id="d1351fn42">Not printed.</note> and Cantel 862 Aug 1.)</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>